{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.23",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 23,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 23 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:1",
      "text": "When you sit down to eat with a ruler, observe carefully what is before you;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:2",
      "text": "and put a knife to your throat if you are a man given to appetite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:3",
      "text": "Do not desire his delicacies, for they are deceptive food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:4",
      "text": "Do not toil to acquire wealth; be wise enough to desist.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:5",
      "text": "When your eyes light upon it, it is gone; for suddenly it takes to itself wings, flying like an eagle toward heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:6",
      "text": "Do not eat the bread of a man who is stingy; do not desire his delicacies;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:7",
      "text": "for he is like one who is inwardly reckoning. “Eat and drink!” he says to you; but his heart is not with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:8",
      "text": "You will vomit up the morsels which you have eaten, and waste your pleasant words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:9",
      "text": "Do not speak in the hearing of a fool, for he will despise the wisdom of your words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:10",
      "text": "Do not remove an ancient landmark or enter the fields of the fatherless;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:11",
      "text": "for their Redeemer is strong; he will plead their cause against you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:12",
      "text": "Apply your mind to instruction and your ear to words of knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:13",
      "text": "Do not withhold discipline from a child; if you beat him with a rod, he will not die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:14",
      "text": "If you beat him with the rod you will save his life from Sheol.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:15",
      "text": "My son, if your heart is wise, my heart too will be glad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:16",
      "text": "My soul will rejoice when your lips speak what is right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:17",
      "text": "Let not your heart envy sinners, but continue in the fear of the Lord all the day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:18",
      "text": "Surely there is a future, and your hope will not be cut off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:19",
      "text": "Hear, my son, and be wise, and direct your mind in the way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:20",
      "text": "Be not among winebibbers, or among gluttonous eaters of meat;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:21",
      "text": "for the drunkard and the glutton will come to poverty, and drowsiness will clothe a man with rags.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:22",
      "text": "Hearken to your father who begot you, and do not despise your mother when she is old.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:23",
      "text": "Buy truth, and do not sell it; buy wisdom, instruction, and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:24",
      "text": "The father of the righteous will greatly rejoice; he who begets a wise son will be glad in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:25",
      "text": "Let your father and mother be glad, let her who bore you rejoice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:26",
      "text": "My son, give me your heart, and let your eyes observe my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:27",
      "text": "For a harlot is a deep pit; an adventuress is a narrow well.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:28",
      "text": "She lies in wait like a robber and increases the faithless among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:29",
      "text": "Who has woe? Who has sorrow? Who has strife? Who has complaining? Who has wounds without cause? Who has redness of eyes?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:30",
      "text": "Those who tarry long over wine, those who go to try mixed wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:31",
      "text": "Do not look at wine when it is red, when it sparkles in the cup and goes down smoothly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:32",
      "text": "At the last it bites like a serpent, and stings like an adder.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:33",
      "text": "Your eyes will see strange things, and your mind utter perverse things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:34",
      "text": "You will be like one who lies down in the midst of the sea, like one who lies on the top of a mast.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.23.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:35",
      "text": "“They struck me,” you will say, “but I was not hurt; they beat me, but I did not feel it. When shall I awake? I will seek another drink.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
